I just finished this wonderful 30 day journey and really enjoyed it and learned from it.  I'm going to redo this journey as I really felt the benefit of daily practice and I've started on another journey of running, am training for a marathon in November, its a mind marathon challenge where we strenghten our minds to make our body strong to complete the marathon.  I have found that my yoga practice has really helped with the running as I haven't ran in over 10 years due to back and hip injuries.  Now I feel strong and ready to take on a marathon challenge in my 50th year so thank you Adriene for your continued presence in my life with daily yoga practice and giving me the courage to take on something totally out of my comfort zone. I've learned to love my body through yoga, particularly through Adriene. I've been regularly practicing for over a year and I feel amazing, feeling myself getting stronger and more flexible. Simple things like Adriene getting us to touch our bellies when breathing has really improved my relationship with my body and love it rather than criticize myself so often. If anyone is in doubt about starting a yoga journey, please do, it has been incredible for my mental health and fitness, plus you have an excuse to buy a cute pair of leggings! It may be hard at first but yoga has got me through some tough times and I really look forward to my time on the mat.

I am so very grateful for the opportunity to experience these 30 days at the beginning of the year with the rest of the community! I have spent the past year exploring all of your videos and have done ALL of the 30 day programs, as I committed myself to a daily yoga practice in 2020. It has helped me to work through a back injury, given me better mobility and strength, helped me to find a deeper sense of self as I have worked on really tough stuff in therapy, and given structure to my day that was desperately needed in this pandemic time. I just published a blog post about my journey this past year, and wanted to share it with you:
https://wellspringenergyworks.com/daily-yoga-practice-reaping-rewards/
Thank you, Adriene, for your beautiful spirit and loving approach. It has made all the difference. Love and Peace.

Hi from Germany 🙋🏻‍♀️ I practice the YWA every day, right at the beginning of the day, early in the morning. I try to practice Yoga for one complete hour, so I do the actual video of the monthly schedule and then afterwards I chose any other of Adriene‘s videos, which has the right length to make a full hour complete. So I know no matter what the day brings, I have done a valuable one hour practice to keep body and mind fit, even if I do not do any other sports / exercise. But if I find the time later during the day, I go power walking or biking in addition to keep me in shape and fit. But I don‘t worry or blame myself, if it is „only the Yoga“ and nothing else. Best wishes to you 🤗
